{
  "stem": "7337.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So Louw said, well, we only allow 75 Polish Jews into the country per year, and that quota is full on the 2nd of January of every year, because the Polish Jews that live in South Africa have family.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they make application to bring their family out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So then my dad said, well, look, I'm the foreman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I come from Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I'm not going to go 16 days by boat to Africa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by the time we get there, the immigration office has got a new directory.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had a book where every town in Europe was listed as to where it was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Lowe checked that book, and Chelmno was not in the book.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, to my dad, that was a great disappointment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He always told me what a wonderful city Chelmno was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, it was a little shtetl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Louw said, well, look, if it's not in the book, then the immigration officer must accept if you say it's Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my dad said, well, I'm not prepared to take that trip, and you have a new edition of your book when I arrive, and then I come back for 16 days.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Eric Louw said, well, one thing I can't get you a-- is a Polish quota.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I know someone in Pretoria who I think, for 35 pounds, can get you a Polish quota.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we sent 35 pounds to some name that I-- I don't remember, and we got the Polish quota for my brother, myself, and my father and came in here as Poles.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And where did you come to?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Johannesburg?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We came to Johannesburg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the first night in Johannesburg, we stayed at the Ritz Hotel in Commissioner Street.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
